bug.short_desc: Procedure search link for a Java code by default points to web app context /source

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 2608 Error screenshot
I have setup an opengrok 0.7 to search a java code base for my product. It works perfectly fine in almost all cases except for the procedure name search from a search result. In an attached image, have a look at red circles. In addres bar it's /trunk but when i took cursor over a method name, it's pointing to /source leading to 404 error being displayed as /source isn't available.
While setting up I have just renamed source.war and updated web.xml with local paths on my server for source and data directory. I have multiple war filed deployed on my server multiple branches of source code. I have kept source as well as data directories separately for each app. source.war and its work dir set up for initial trials is completely removed from tomcat.
You need to use "-w context-name" when you run opengrok to provide another name than source.
